        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 5:48PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles south of Blowing Rock, or 4 miles south of Blowing Rock In
Caldwell County, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lenoir, Blowing Rock In Caldwell County, Cedar Rock, Grandfather
Mountain State Park, B.R. Parkway-Linville Falls To Grandfather,
Globe, Patterson, Upton, and Edgemont.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
